
**If you're using a desktop environment and want the script to run upon GUI login:**

**Create a .desktop entry:**

## Create A desktop File 
nano ~/.config/autostart/stockselector.desktop
## Add the following content:

[Desktop Entry]
Type=Application
Exec=/usr/bin/python3 /home/janardan/StockScrappingProject/StockSelectorStartUpScript.py
Hidden=false
NoDisplay=false
X-GNOME-Autostart-enabled=true
Name=Stock Selector Script
Comment=Run stock selector script on login


## Save the file and restart your session.

Exec is the file to start the script


